@node "theory" "theory"
@{b}@{u}THEORY@{ub}@{uu}

    Studies  have  shown  that  sensory  input  consisting  of visual and
aural patterns  of co-ordinated frequencies can affect the function of the
brain.  If the  frequency  starts  at  your "dominant frequency" and slowly
changes it can entrain your brain to a new "beat frequency". Of  course the
entire brain doesn't operate on a single frequency. However EEGs  show  that
at any moment, the brain produces waveforms in four frequency groupings:

                 Beta waves (14-30Hz)
                 Alpha waves (8-13Hz)
                 Theta waves (4-7Hz)
                 Delta waves (1-3Hz)

    Now,  usually one of these is the dominant frequency (producing the
highest amplitude  on  the  EEG).   Usually,  the  mind is in the beta
state, signalling alertness.   Also,  the  higher  the  subject's  stress
level, the higher the frequency  of  beta waves.  Alpha fequencies are
associated with meditation and relaxation.   Theta  waves  are  related  to
creative influences and dreamlike states, and delta waves are associated
with sleep.
@endnode

@node "intro" "intro"
@{b}@{u}INTRODUCTION@{ub}@{uu}

  Since the beginning of time, man has found new ways to alter his state of
awareness. This would include using drugs, which can be dangerous and
expensive, and for some; exercise. The release of certain brain chemicals
alter our mood, the way we think and feel and many other aspects of our
daily lives.

  The altering of reality occurred with stone-age man, through wild plants
such as Marijuana and Psilocybe mushrooms. The same practices are used today
with many of the same drugs. If you have ever watched a child start to turn
around and around until they quite literally fall down, you know that even
at this early stage in life there is some sort of satisfaction from escaping
reality.

  Enter Genos Mind Machine. By simply watching the computer screen in a
darkened room. Your brain will begin to "harmonize" with the flashes of
light on the screen. There are different speeds to coincide with the
different brain waves in the human body. Through allowing your brain to
simulate different brain wave patterns, you are to achieve different levels
of altered states. At last, a perfectly legal answer to the "natural high".
@endnode

